The paper discusses the use of satellite imagery and image-based features to predict housing prices, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the importance of data availability and sampling strategies, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for integrating satellite-based metrics with standard survey data, which could fall under social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
